oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Twenty-Fourth Annual Conference (1991). Annual Business and Awards Luncheon Meeting
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The Annual Business and Awards Luncheon Meeting was held on Saturday, September 21, with Dr. David McClary presiding. Dr. Harold Amstutz, Executive Vice President stated that 1,328 attended the meeting, including 616 veterinarians. The AABP was honored with the attendance and participation of A VMA President-Elect L. Everett Macomber, Centralia, Washington and Dr. Pierre Lekeux, Liege, Belgium, Secretary of the World Association for Buiatrics.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1991; xv-xvii
